b'     Dear Students,       Link       TU Berlin Summer University    The TU Berlin Summer and Winter University is looking forward to launching its first 2017 winter program, welcoming international students to the German capital for four weeks of academic study at the Berlin Institute of Technology (TU Berlin).  The following courses will start from January 3rd 2017:  CanSat: Handson Satellite Design a  A CanSat is a small satellite in shape of a commercial beverage can that performs several measuring tasks. In this course, a CanSat is designed, built and tested in the field during a rocket launch.  Programming in Java  In this course students will learn how to write computer programs in the programming language Java. Students will work individually and in groups, with the course culminating in a big project at the end.  Startup Crash Course: From Idea to Reality  This course is for budding entrepreneurs who want to gain insight into launching a startup. Participants will learn theory, have guest talks from startup owners in Berlin, and will work on their own business models in groups, which they will pitch to investors in a mock investor pitch.  TU Berlin will also be running the third 2017 summer program, from June to August, with many wide range of courses. Please click here  for more information.  You can also learn more about us on the  website  and social media channels such as  Facebook . Find the full course list  here . Registration is  online  now!     Mr. Arvind Sivamani  Liaison Officer (Outgoing Students)  International Relations  Office of International Relations l 2 nd Floor, IC & SR Building  Indian Institute of Technology Madras l Chennai  600 036 l INDIA  Tel: (91) 0442257 4928  Email: oir4@wmail.iitm.ac.in   Website:       '

